	 ('bf994aae-6527-4cd3-b651-172e7558e928'::uuid,'Third-World-Skeptical-Kid','This meme template features a candid interaction between two individuals in what appears to be a rural or village setting. The focal point is a young African boy, probably around 5-7 years old, wearing a striped polo shirt. His expression is particularly noteworthy - he has a skeptical, slightly dubious look on his face, with his eyes narrowed and his mouth slightly pursed. This expression conveys a sense of disbelief or suspicion, which is central to the meme''s humor and usage.

Beside him is a woman with long dark hair, visible only in profile. She seems to be leaning in or speaking to the boy, though her exact expression isn''t visible. The contrast between her presence and the boy''s reaction creates the comedic tension in the image.

The background suggests a simple, possibly impoverished environment. There''s a thatched or straw wall visible, and the ground appears to be bare earth. This setting adds context to the interaction, implying perhaps a aid worker or volunteer speaking with a local child.

The composition of the image is intimate, with a close-up view that emphasizes the boy''s expressive face. The lighting is natural, giving the scene an authentic, unposed quality.

This meme is often used to express skepticism, disbelief, or a "yeah, right" attitude in response to dubious claims or explanations. The boy''s face has become iconic for conveying that "I''m not buying what you''re selling" sentiment in a variety of contexts online.

The image captures a moment of cross-cultural interaction, which adds layers of potential interpretation depending on how it''s used. It''s a versatile template that can be applied to many situations where someone is unconvinced by what they''re hearing or experiencing.','/memes/Third-World-Skeptical-Kid.jpg',2,'{}','{"African skeptical child","so your telling me","so you''re telling me","skeptical african kid",full,"so your telling me......","african boy","\"so you mean to tell me\" meme template"}',0.0,'[0.032195043,-0.017052146,-0.0036037301,0.028611135,0.012775432,-0.056494363,-0.0048244596,-0.0032796855,-0.007778703,0.03136585,0.009141104,-0.011682066,0.027941722,0.019318298,-0.023179809,-0.004573271,0.010430253,-0.01894204,0.014626767,-0.0032866122,0.003962093,0.0029609255,-0.069115035,-0.026730416,-0.014630387,0.05347323,0.007805691,-0.0040547345,0.06603358,0.04828725,0.0031015945,0.033990983,0.010764213,-0.025929585,-0.0044988403,-0.018282123,0.04423684,-0.042963717,-0.046604887,-0.024924612,0.0026882142,-0.0029705083,0.0333813,-0.0032162918,-0.039059427,-0.014009256,0.000619113,-0.031870324,0.041443724,0.030048613,0.021527763,-0.020943047,0.029977508,-0.00033383662,-0.042736255,-0.05382793,-0.0044989246,-0.007348845,0.012528056,0.01590744,0.033649363,0.007894874,0.021068703,-0.057843767,-0.019366754,0.0043048253,-0.036745846,-0.003600898,-0.023237823,-0.025729194,-0.008654373,0.023573127,-0.0028969033,-0.019298136,-0.0124086505,-0.005279242,-0.02575098,-0.0039051862,0.023875356,0.023942094,0.054739103,0.038094003,0.01985694,-0.03517385,-0.026750201,-0.0050504818,0.026057107,0.015963396,0.0008646868,-0.005126592,0.004440877,0.04171107,-0.025579456,-0.016653342,0.039312277,0.04961726,-0.0038372332,0.024128137,0.00069977547,0.009763973,-0.009008994,0.045217056,-0.029163623,0.035348155,-0.023964386,0.008740343,0.016679693,-0.034752473,-0.05575759,-0.019673679,-0.0003402125,-0.039974827,0.001677165,-0.020275136,-0.019431898,0.055090204,-0.005007011,0.021877326,-