	 ('9a0deec0-8d69-40cc-8853-86e06acc7da4'::uuid,'That-Would-Be-Great','This meme template comes from a scene in the 1999 comedy film "Office Space," which satirizes corporate office culture. The image shows a middle-aged man in typical 1990s office attire standing in a cubicle-filled workspace. He''s wearing a light blue button-up shirt, red suspenders, and a yellow patterned tie. Large, square-framed glasses dominate his face, emphasizing his stereotypical "nerdy" appearance.

The man''s expression is one of exasperation or frustration, with his mouth slightly open as if he''s in the middle of speaking or reacting to something. His hair is neatly combed but has a slightly disheveled look, adding to the sense of stress or annoyance.

In his hand, he''s holding a white coffee mug, a common prop in office environments. The background shows a typical open-plan office space with fluorescent lighting, beige walls, and glimpses of other cubicles and office workers.

This image is often used as a reaction meme to express frustration, disbelief, or sarcastic agreement in workplace-related contexts or when dealing with bureaucratic absurdities. The character''s look and posture embody the essence of a put-upon office worker dealing with the mundane trials of corporate life.

