	 ('a96b1898-5964-48c7-999c-fd1bf0b497fc'::uuid,'Bad-Luck-Brian','This meme template features a portrait-style photograph of a young man, likely in his teens, set against a purple studio backdrop. The image has the aesthetic of a school yearbook photo from the late 1990s or early 2000s.

The subject is wearing a distinctive outfit that contributes significantly to the meme''s recognizable look: a red plaid sweater vest over a light blue collared shirt. This combination gives off a nerdy or preppy vibe that''s central to the meme''s humor.

The young man has short, neatly combed strawberry blond hair. His facial expression is the focal point of the image - he''s sporting an exaggerated, toothy grin that stretches across his entire face. This smile appears somewhat forced or awkward, which is a key element of the meme''s appeal. His eyes are wide open, adding to the overall impression of enthusiasm or nervousness.

The lighting in the photo is typical of professional portrait photography, with the subject well-lit against the darker background. This creates a stark contrast that further emphasizes the subject''s facial features and expression.

This image has become iconic in meme culture, often used to represent awkwardness, social ineptitude, or ironic enthusiasm. It''s frequently captioned with text describing socially uncomfortable situations or naive misunderstandings, playing off the subject''s appearance and expression.

The meme is sometimes referred to as "Bad Luck Brian" in popular culture, though per instructions, I''m not identifying the individual. Its enduring popularity stems from its ability to encapsulate a particular type of teenage awkwardness that many find relatable or humorously cringe-worthy.','/memes/Bad-Luck-Brian.jpg',2,'{}','{"bad luck brian nerdy","bad luck brian cry","unlucky ginger kid","loser boy"}',0.0,'[0.03487671,-0.04073023,0.01615763,0.019325042,0.023105523,-0.026794555,0.00011304224,-0.014192917,-0.007929009,0.026978826,0.006923735,-0.043483607,0.041930564,-0.0011161853,-0.0046460438,-0.014506039,0.0010748402,-0.03284747,-0.05678694,0.021748379,0.015206983,-0.0038979226,-0.04697934,-0.026322702,0.021743985,0.036851805,0.0131429285,0.017805152,0.047296375,0.0129228085,0.0064809197,0.005132333,-0.02849629,-0.031588547,0.011450689,0.01965621,0.049645163,-0.040966116,-0.002204225,-0.0029965157,0.034998868,-0.019224834,0.016529469,-0.000406849,-0.015470863,-0.03364158,-0.016499173,-0.008957109,0.051181406,0.0043856,0.004203493,-0.042968728,0.005877289,0.04168417,0.012820265,-0.02662516,0.009819304,0.0007448252,0.030869331,0.029699009,0.012822404,0.021630451,-0.0019163812,-0.048586935,-0.030323835,0.0028831405,-0.010217974,0.01118545,-0.005742407,-0.01291737,-0.0037653456,0.00511623,-0.005016708,0.02984243,-0.0249734,-0.028362952,-0.04105395,-0.0092299,0.018842708,0.028651258,0.05246233,0.025893793,0.006217869,-0.037131105,-0.018751716,-0.013748982,0.019207234,0.049683716,-0.0061898762,-0.0212292,-0.00050824194,0.058030948,-0.03262645,0.0033780278,0.024184639,0.01687479,0.009871908,0.021592174,-0.005658184,0.004099754,0.011655361,0.049695402,-0.03080669,0.03748012,-0.054183464,0.012798274,0.032718405,-0.014361895,-0.064173914,-0.03386723,0.016613757,-0.02793834,0.006268047,-0.020100288,-0.053202983,0.026342418,-0.0026180476,0.04501346,-0.016338693,-0.019503273,-0.030899327,-0.008947967,-0.011084312,-0.025189282,-0.0150390975,-0.0028631818,0.00994643,0.0445559