	 ('32340e66-5f5b-4511-aad3-679c0ecef94c'::uuid,'Who-Killed-Hannibal','This meme template consists of two panels from what appears to be a comedy sketch or show on Adult Swim, as indicated by the watermark.

In the top panel, we see a talk show-like set with a distinctive red, geometrically patterned backdrop. The main focus is on a man in a light gray suit and tie standing to the right. He''s holding a gun, pointing it at someone lying on a couch to the left. The person on the couch appears to be slumped over or possibly unconscious, wearing a blue shirt and dark pants. There''s a small table with a globe visible in the background, adding to the talk show aesthetic.

The bottom panel shows the same scene moments later. The man in the suit is now facing the camera with a perplexed or concerned expression. His arm is lowered, no longer holding the gun visibly. The person on the couch remains in the same position, and a small amount of smoke can be seen, presumably from the discharged firearm.

The juxtaposition of these two images creates a sense of sudden realization or regret after an impulsive action. The talk show setting contrasted with the violent act adds an element of absurdist humor typical of Adult Swim programming.

This template is often used to represent situations where someone acts rashly and then immediately questions or regrets their decision, with the gunshot representing an irreversible action and the confused look embodying the subsequent "What have I done?" moment.

The meme''s power comes from its ability to humorously portray the universal experience of instant regret following a hasty decision, albeit in an exaggerated, darkly comic manner.','/memes/Who-Killed-Hannibal.jpg',2,'{}','{"Eric Andre shooting Hannibal Buress","why would they do this","eric andre meme","why would do this"}',0.0,'[0.01248751,-0.016039856,0.0005798272,0.035904143,0.011749349,-0.076244794,-0.07384853,0.0006512695,-0.0043778797,0.036272656,0.018445747,0.018336035,0.04046707,-0.008251276,-0.009937632,0.027124383,-0.0061947107,0.0057281265,-0.034112077,0.03921209,0.008408416,-0.03757624,-0.07425169,-0.010003126,-0.010047718,0.0111560235,-0.018798245,0.022235133,0.041545346,0.020200875,0.008532027,-0.02423583,-0.01427461,-0.05935179,0.005902634,-0.0014294563,0.023761252,-0.035414636,-0.0012924767,-0.022358818,0.0010140055,0.0046985378,0.051621426,-0.029550133,-0.031173583,-0.02306962,-0.017801559,-0.0058640786,-0.01860682,0.004662729,0.03698583,-0.009216655,0.017430602,-0.00022475472,-0.02988196,-0.056899194,-0.041263737,-0.019905448,0.015250625,0.0006151024,0.03931376,0.006160694,-0.034233388,-0.052608345,-0.020586308,0.024113148,-0.014182815,0.007350007,-0.037725423,0.015514703,0.014722097,0.008734637,-0.0027882094,0.02626731,-0.011363725,0.014513341,-0.011185877,-0.026430173,0.047204226,-0.018881734,0.020912785,0.04972764,0.025194127,-0.023802524,-0.011814874,-0.0274549,0.02710951,0.028321177,0.03918101,-0.028679054,-0.005761759,0.05382281,-0.009148789,-0.0070540933,0.025166988,0.037291702,-0.0007322571,0.012606625,0.0003835984,-0.029727718,-0.019926034,0.022022447,-0.045233935,0.018329306,-0.046965927,0.027576592,0.062210035,0.00584288,-0.0182984,-0.047487427,0.025666073,-0.0028616956,0.012334427,0.015194909,-0.009854469,0.051028777,-0.026344268,0.025963992,-0.060566407,-0.016383305,-0.034672398,0.009611588,-0.015107596,0.0013442053,0.00808653,-0.034146417,0.041227605,0.042470988,-0.0336436,0.0380881,0.006510613,-0.032401007,0.0014431102,0.001319501,-