	 ('c034e9fb-fe03-44da-be13-4cfed2e7c893'::uuid,'Who-Would-Win','This meme template is a minimalist design that invites comparison or competition between two subjects. The image is predominantly white, creating a clean, stark background that draws attention to its simple yet effective structure.

At the top of the image, in bold black capital letters, is the question "WHO WOULD WIN?" This text acts as the title or prompt for the meme, setting up the premise of a hypothetical contest or comparison.

Directly below the text is a thick horizontal black line that spans the width of the image. This line serves to separate the title from the content area below.

The lower portion of the image is divided into two equal sections by a vertical black line that extends from the horizontal line to the bottom of the frame. This creates two blank white spaces on either side of the dividing line.

The layout is reminiscent of a simple tournament bracket or versus matchup, encouraging viewers to mentally fill in the blank spaces with competing entities, concepts, or scenarios. The stark contrast and minimalist design make it highly adaptable for various humorous or thought-provoking comparisons.

This template''s simplicity allows for easy modification and insertion of text or images into the blank spaces, making it a versatile format for creating memes across a wide range of topics and contexts. Its clean design also ensures that added content will stand out clearly, focusing the viewer''s attention on the comparison being made.

The "Who Would Win?" format has become a popular way to humorously pit unlikely opponents against each other or to compare vastly different concepts, often with absurd or unexpected results. This template''s enduring popularity in meme culture speaks to its effectiveness in sparking engagement and discussion through visual comparison.','/memes/Who-Would-Win.jpg',2,'{}','{}',0.0,'[0.006995643,-0.033124376,0.015331416,0.0024417737,-0.0025983613,-0.05452937,-0.071667925,-0.004850254,-0.020689499,0.041517247,-0.0004997132,0.018432973,0.0316639,0.004220516,-0.020264585,-0.025544498,-0.016140288,-0.028101666,-0.027981067,-0.018002689,-0.0125904465,0.033462964,-0.082583435,-0.03395158,0.0134920515,0.025461394,-0.0056215813,0.020372108,0.056190714,0.0168836,-0.008128966,-0.019307934,-0.006308293,-0.053430986,-0.023581186,-0.013397367,0.03466111,-0.0452045,-0.044549875,-0.0053057624,0.029748252,-0.025465967,0.018787043,-0.005832659,-0.047110472,-0.017158963,-0.02208646,-0.0014062056,-0.012384582,-0.038748316,-0.0160105,-0.026893107,0.02318657,-0.018978637,-0.03053707,0.0013941464,-0.013577764,-0.013872674,-0.017111178,0.06474547,0.044693504,0.015321835,0.017465241,-0.04537583,-0.008042992,-0.020689331,0.03075031,-0.02640446,-0.0075916024,0.0010616414,-0.020751292,-0.01813893,-0.03507752,-0.019355537,-0.03663265,-0.008556457,-0.013980602,-0.0398032,0.0068827537,0.022004638,0.019082656,0.08743099,0.0024280534,-0.03129845,-0.039749004,-0.021481615,0.030519484,0.0007078978,0.019603832,-0.03526347,-0.028710313,0.05401205,0.0024837628,0.017684205,0.018009279,0.023832675,-0.011071968,0.029208012,-0.0031242585,0.003401547,0.02775353,0.04530917,-0.022640789,0.046629928,-0.049436897,0.024873896,0.0025733395,-0.008274562,-0.05294097,-0.03440284,0.0122411,-0.0087830555,-0.007466352,0.012574797,-0.020088425,0.026561491,0.018449886,0.07147224,-0.0557609,0.009855088,-0.056133203,0.014808883,-0.049293175,0.010785469,-0.023832042,-0.0037776425,-0.0042831083,0.018145898,-0.029234873,-0.011818