	 ('4f75b269-926e-4f99-b0b4-e0175c2de83b'::uuid,'Uncle-Sam','This image depicts the iconic "Uncle Sam" figure, a personification of the United States government that has been used in various contexts since the early 19th century. The image shows a stern-faced older man with a pointed beard and intense, piercing eyes looking directly at the viewer. He''s wearing the characteristic Uncle Sam costume: a tall top hat with a blue band decorated with white stars, a white shirt with a red bow tie, and a dark blue jacket.

The most striking feature of this image is the man''s intense, almost accusatory expression, emphasized by his furrowed brow and the way he''s leaning slightly forward. His right hand is extended towards the viewer, with his index finger pointing directly out of the image. This gesture, combined with his stern gaze, creates a powerful sense of direct address and engagement with the viewer.

The color scheme is patriotic, featuring the red, white, and blue of the American flag. The painting style appears to be a vintage illustration, with bold brushstrokes and a slightly faded, classic look that evokes mid-20th century propaganda posters.

This image is famous for its use in U.S. Army recruiting posters with the slogan "I Want YOU for U.S. Army" during World Wars I and II. As a meme template, it''s often used to convey a sense of direct appeal, accusation, or call to action, playing on its original recruitment purpose. The pointing gesture and intense gaze make it particularly effective for creating a sense of personal responsibility or involvement in the viewer.

The image cuts off at about chest level, focusing all attention on the man''s face and pointing gesture. This cropping intensifies the confrontational nature of the image, making it an impactful and versatile template for various meme contexts, often used to make humorous or satirical points about responsibility, patriotism, or social commentary.','/memes/Uncle-Sam.jpg',2,'{}','{USA,murica,"i want you for us army!","we want you","i want you","thank you!","we need you","usa needs you","i need you","uncle sam pointing finger"}',0.0,'[0.037394535,-0.025980683,0.022797244,0.040435728,0.006200623,-0.028337775,-0.023749929,0.001633762,-0.008926453,0.026742587,0.0018868734,-0.03261206,0.016945608,0.022686556,0.020935034,0.027204873,0.0062833168,0.002277456,0.025870154,0.014386154,-0.0022891387,-0.015369204,-0.049179256,-0.033999816,-0.008292801,0.047773942,-0.000699047,0.026872324,0.050114144,0.01927775,-0.004854054,-0.014837798,-0.026965747,-0.057954505,-0.011033857,-0.019648273,0.04227785,-0.10152472,0.01969436,-0.04589799,0.03431109,-0.013468773,0.005211785,-0.005155743,-0.044372804,-0.029610094,-0.039906617,-0.06719485,0.024697628,-0.0063017975,-0.0027074295,-0.014000012,-0.007178042,0.036425214,0.00064328394,-0.03038741,0.0021924942,-0.040110953,0.0016074057,0.028423777,0.028716076,-0.013143438,-0.00011000118,-0.04911736,-0.04639956,-0.020071972,-0.020282269,0.025048776,-0.0069633066,0.028883392,0.00046617314,-0.0073528835,0.048289593,-0.018075602,-0.026163297,0.014991248,-0.014685336,-0.026847366,0.007079428,0.006635461,0.002118761,0.019408695,-0.01586839,-0.024658104,0.016555127,0.04299884,0.018420948,0.029452115,0.022315599,-0.02372183,-0.006249974,0.030432615,-0.033366434,0.0010362869,0.015935894,0.018969487,-0.009473621,0.03709563,0.030823322,-0.010948424,-0.00037443312,0.025602153,-0.0076895603,0.030728238,-0.041260798,0.019704819,-0.0041763736,-0.026060335,-0.0133576915,-0.050946318,0.021727724,-0.01640782,0.019826962,-0.022013238,-0.086166754,0.008661437,-0.01